<FlowDocument PagePadding="5,0,5,0" AllowDrop="True" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"><Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="16">Data Binding</Paragraph><Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14">Data can be bound to a chart in different ways. The following list details the various methods of data binding.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14"><Bold>ObservableCollection Binding Demo</Bold>-Demonstrates binding data from an observable collection</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14"><Bold>CollectionViewSource Demo</Bold>-Demonstrates how a chart listens to changes in the Collection View Source and automatically updates</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14"><Bold>LINQ Data Binding Demo</Bold>-Illustrates directly assigning LINQ results as a chart series data source</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14"><Bold>IList Data Binding Demo</Bold>-Illustrates binding an <Run FontWeight="Bold">IList</Run> collection to the <Run FontWeight="Bold">Datasource</Run> property of the class <Run FontWeight="Bold">Chart Series</Run></Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14"><Bold>XML Data Binding Demo</Bold>-Illustrates binding a XML data provider to the <Run FontWeight="Bold">Datasource</Run> property of the class <Run FontWeight="Bold">Chart Series</Run></Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14" xml:space="preserve"><Bold>DataTable Binding Demo</Bold>-Demonstrates binding data from a database </Paragraph>

</FlowDocument>